&lt;p&gt;Band 6 Junior Sister/Charge Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a RN with considerable accident and emergency experience and ready for a new leadership challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for band 6 junior sisters/charge nurses to join our friendly committed team at Hillingdon hospital. You will need excellent communication and organisational skills, be self-motivated, flexible and ready to develop your leadership skills within a supportive, empowering department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work alongside the Matron and senior sisters to deliver a caring and innovative service across all aspects of the Emergency department. You will act as shift leader ensuring the safety and patient flow of the department liaising with multi-disciplinary teams, adhering to the Hillingdon hospital’s CARES values and ensuring these are upheld by the rest of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also include teaching and assisting with the development of junior staff. A mentorship qualification would be an ideal for this post to assist with our regular intake of students and newly qualified nursing staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An informal visit is strongly recommended.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Katrina Warkcup Matron on 07467335851.&lt;/p&gt;
